document OutputsAndSchemas: "Outputs And Schemas"
    """This reference teaches how a turn emits its answer. `output` declares the
artifact contract. `output shape` decides what kind of artifact it is. `output
schema` owns the typed JSON payload for structured finals. `final_output:` on
an agent marks one emitted `TurnResponse` output as the turn-ending assistant
message.

Keep outputs small and typed. Prefer an `output schema` block over prose when
the host needs exact fields. Prefer one routed `route field` over a second
`route_from` table when the final JSON itself owns the route choice.

Read the source of truth in this order before you ship code:"""

    bullets sources:
        "`doctrine/grammars/doctrine.lark`"
        "`docs/LANGUAGE_REFERENCE.md` (output and output schema sections)"
        "`docs/AGENT_IO_DESIGN_NOTES.md`"

    section output_declaration_shape: "Output Declaration Shape"
        "A minimal prose output:"
        code:
            language: prompt-fragment
            text: """output ReviewComment: "Review Comment"
    target: TurnResponse
    shape: Comment
    requirement: Required
"""
        "Important rules:"
        bullets rules:
            "An output uses either `target` plus `shape`, or a titled `files:` section."
            """Built-in targets used in the shipped corpus include `TurnResponse` and
  `File`. Custom targets can be declared with `output target`."""
            "Output shapes can be named with `output shape`."
            """`schema:` on `output` attaches a Doctrine `schema` declaration for
  schema-owned sections, gates, and artifacts."""
            """`schema:` on `output shape` remains the owner-aware attachment point for
  `output schema` when the shape kind is `JsonObject`."""
            """A markdown-bearing `output` may not attach both `schema:` and `structure:`.
  Pick exactly one artifact owner."""
            "`structure:` on a markdown-bearing output attaches a named `document`."
            """`render_profile:` may attach to a markdown-bearing output when exactly one
  output artifact owns the markdown contract."""
            """`outputs` blocks group outputs and bind them under local keys for a
  concrete turn."""

        "Output bodies may also contain:"
        bullets body_items:
            "authored fields and sections"
            "readable declaration refs"
            """readable block kinds such as `definitions`, `properties`, `table`,
  explicit `guard` shells, `callout`, `code`, raw `markdown`, raw `html`,
  `footnotes`, and `image`"""
            "guarded output items like `next_owner: route.next_owner when route.exists`"
            """keyed guarded sections like
  `failure_detail: \"Failure Detail\" when verdict == ReviewVerdict.changes_requested:`"""
            "`trust_surface`"
            "`standalone_read`"

        section output_targets_and_delivery_skills: "Output Targets And Delivery Skills"
            """A custom `output target` may bind one reusable delivery skill with
`delivery_skill:`. Put delivery behavior on the target, not on each output."""
            code:
                language: prompt-fragment
                text: """skill LedgerNoteDelivery: "ledger-note-delivery"
    purpose: "Append markdown notes to the shared ledger."

output target LedgerNoteAppend: "Ledger Note Append"
    delivery_skill: LedgerNoteDelivery
    required: "Required"
        ledger_id: "Ledger ID"

output LedgerNote: "Ledger Note"
    target: LedgerNoteAppend
        ledger_id: "current-ledger"
    shape: MarkdownDocument
    requirement: Advisory
"""
            """The emitted contract table renders one `Delivered Via` row after `Target` and
before target config rows."""

    section output_schema_shape: "Output Schema Shape"
        """`output schema` owns the machine-readable payload fields for structured
`JsonObject` outputs. Attach it through `schema:` on an `output shape` with
`kind: JsonObject`."""
        code:
            language: prompt-fragment
            text: """enum RepoStatus: "Repo Status"
    ok: "OK"
    action_required: "Action Required"

output schema RepoStatusSchema: "Repo Status Schema"
    field summary: "Summary"
        type: string
        note: "Short natural-language status."

    field status: "Status"
        type: RepoStatus
        note: "Current repo outcome."

    field next_step: "Next Step"
        type: string
        nullable
        note: "Null when no follow-up is needed."

    example:
        summary: "Branch is clean and checks passed."
        status: "ok"
        next_step: null


output shape RepoStatusJson: "Repo Status JSON"
    kind: JsonObject
    schema: RepoStatusSchema


output RepoStatusFinalResponse: "Repo Status Final Response"
    target: TurnResponse
    shape: RepoStatusJson
    requirement: Required
"""
        """See `examples/79_final_output_output_schema` for the smallest shipped
structured final, including inheritance and an `example:` block."""

        section field_shapes: "Field Shapes"
            "The shipped field shapes are:"
            bullets field_forms:
                "`field <key>: \"Title\"` with a `type:` line and optional `note:`."
                "`route field <key>: \"Title\"` with routed enum-style members (see below)."
                """`def <key>: \"Title\"` for reusable nested object defs referenced by `items:`
  or `any_of`."""

            "Type intrinsics:"
            bullets intrinsics:
                "`type: string`"
                "`type: number`"
                "`type: integer`"
                "`type: boolean`"
                """`type: <EnumName>` for a closed vocabulary. Declare the enum once
  with `enum EnumName: "..."` and one member per value, then write
  `type: EnumName` on the field. See `examples/139_enum_typed_field_bodies`."""
                "`type: object` with nested `field` lines or an `any_of:` block"

            "Range and shape constraints:"
            bullets constraints:
                "`min_length: <n>` / `max_length: <n>`"
                "`minimum: <n>` / `maximum: <n>`"
                "`exclusive_minimum: <n>` / `exclusive_maximum: <n>`"
                "`multiple_of: <n>`"
                "`format: <name>`"
                "`pattern: \"<regex>\"`"
                "`const: <literal>`"
                "`items: <NameRef>` or `items:` indented block for typed array elements"
                "`any_of:` with one or more `variant <Key>:` blocks"

            "Nullability:"
            bullets nullability:
                "Use `nullable` when an `output schema` field or route field may be `null`."
                """`required` and `optional` are retired inside `output schema`. Doctrine still
  parses them there only so it can raise targeted upgrade errors (see
  `docs/COMPILER_ERRORS.md` entries E236 and E237)."""
                "Doctrine does not ship `?` shorthand for `output schema` fields."

            "Enums:"
            bullets enums:
                """Doctrine 5.0 ships exactly one canonical form for field
  vocabularies: declare `enum EnumName: "..."` once, then write
  `type: EnumName` on the field. The same form applies to readable
  `row_schema` entries, readable `item_schema` entries, readable table
  columns, and record scalars."""
                """The inline `type: enum` + `values:` form and the legacy
  `type: string` + `enum:` form are deleted in 5.0. Typing against an
  unknown enum name fails loud with `E320`."""

        section example_blocks: "Example Blocks"
            """`output schema` may declare an optional `example:` block. When present,
Doctrine validates it against the schema and renders an `Example` section on
the structured final output. If `example:` is omitted, the structured final
still emits; the `Example` section is simply skipped."""

        section output_shape_inheritance: "Output Shape Inheritance"
            """`output shape` may inherit from another shape with `output shape
Child[Parent]: \"Title\"`. Use `inherit kind` to keep the parent's shape kind
and `override schema:` to swap the attached `output schema`."""
            code:
                language: prompt
                text: """output shape RepoStatusJson[BaseRepoStatusJson]: "Repo Status JSON"
    inherit kind
    override schema: RepoStatusSchema
"""

    section output_inheritance: "Output Inheritance"
        """Inherited outputs use the same explicit patching style Doctrine uses
elsewhere."""
        code:
            language: prompt
            text: """output BaseReply: "Base Reply"
    target: TurnResponse
    shape: Comment
    requirement: Required

    summary: "Summary"
        "Summarize the shipped result."


output LessonsLeadOutput[BaseReply]: "Lessons Lead Output"
    inherit {target, shape, requirement, summary}

    hit: "Test"
        "blah blah blah"
"""
        "Important rules:"
        bullets inheritance_rules:
            "`output Child[Parent]: \"Title\"` inherits from another `output`."
            "`inherit key` keeps one inherited top-level output entry."
            "`inherit {target, shape, requirement}` keeps several in authored order."
            "`override key:` replaces one inherited top-level output entry."
            """Top-level keys such as `target`, `shape`, `requirement`, `schema`,
  `structure`, `render_profile`, `trust_surface`, and `standalone_read` follow
  the same explicit `inherit` or `override` model."""
            "Children must account for every inherited top-level key exactly once."
            "Inherited parent outputs must use stable keyed top-level items only."
            """`outputs[...]` block inheritance is separate from `output[...]` declaration
  inheritance."""
            """v1 output inheritance is top-level only. If you need to change
  `current_truth.invalidations`, override `current_truth` and rewrite that
  whole top-level section."""

        "See these shipped examples:"
        bullets shipped:
            "`examples/107_output_inheritance_basic` — smallest inherited output."
            """`examples/108_output_inheritance_attachments` — inherited `render_profile`,
  `trust_surface`, and `standalone_read`."""
            """`examples/109_imported_review_handoff_output_inheritance` — imported
  reusable handoff output inherited and extended locally."""
            """`examples/110_final_output_inherited_output` — inherited output used
  through `final_output:`."""
            """`examples/111_inherited_output_route_semantics` — inherited output keeping
  shared `route.*` readback."""
            """`examples/112_output_inheritance_fail_loud` — fail-loud errors when
  accounting is wrong."""

    section final_output_section: "final_output"
        """`final_output:` on an agent designates one emitted `TurnResponse` output as
the final assistant message. That output renders under a dedicated `Final
Output` section and is omitted from ordinary `Outputs` rendering for that
agent.

Short form:"""
        code:
            language: prompt-fragment
            text: """final_output: RepoStatusFinalResponse
"""
        "Block form with route binding:"
        code:
            language: prompt-fragment
            text: """final_output:
    output: WriterDecision
    route: next_route
"""
        "Block form on a review-driven agent:"
        code:
            language: prompt-fragment
            text: """final_output:
    output: AcceptanceControlFinalResponse
    review_fields:
        verdict
        current_artifact: current_artifact
        next_owner
"""
        "Important rules:"
        bullets final_output_rules:
            """When the designated output's `output shape` carries an `output schema`, the
  final assistant message is structured JSON."""
            """On review-driven agents, the designated final output may be either the
  review's `comment_output:` or a second emitted `TurnResponse`."""
            """`comment_output:` stays the review carrier even when `final_output:` points
  at a second output."""
            """A `review_fields:` binding accepts bare identity binds like `next_owner`
  when the final-output field key matches the review semantic name."""
            """The compiler emits whether a split final response is `control_ready`.
  Authors do not declare that mode by hand."""

        """See `examples/79_final_output_output_schema` for the smallest structured
final. See `examples/87_workflow_route_output_binding` for a workflow-law
ordinary final with shared `route.*` readback."""

    section route_fields: "Route Fields"
        """A structured final output may declare a first-class routed owner with `route
field`. The route field owns the route choice keys, labels, and named target
agents in one place. It lowers to an ordinary string enum on the wire."""
        code:
            language: prompt
            text: """output schema WriterDecisionSchema: "Writer Decision Schema"
    route field next_route: "Next Route"
        seek_muse: "Send to Muse for fresh inspiration." -> Muse
        ready_for_critic: "Send to PoemCritic for judgment." -> PoemCritic

    field summary: "Summary"
        type: string


agent Writer:
    role: "Choose the next owner from the final output itself."
    outputs: "Outputs"
        WriterDecision
    final_output:
        output: WriterDecision
        route: next_route
"""
        """See `examples/120_route_field_final_output_contract` for the full route-field
pattern."""

        section nullable_route_fields: "Nullable Route Fields"
            """Add `nullable` on a `route field` when `null` means \"no handoff on this
turn.\" The emitted route contract still carries `route.selector` with the
bound field path and null behavior."""
            code:
                language: prompt
                text: """enum TurnResultKind: "Turn Result Kind"
    handoff: "Handoff"
    done: "Done"

output schema WriterTurnResultSchema: "Writer Turn Result Schema"
    route field next_route: "Next Route"
        revise_more: "Send to RevisionPartner for one more pass." -> RevisionPartner
        nullable
        note: "Use null when the writer can finish without a handoff."

    field kind: "Kind"
        type: TurnResultKind

    field summary: "Summary"
        type: string
"""
            """See `examples/121_nullable_route_field_final_output_contract` for the
shipped proof of null-means-no-handoff behavior."""

        section route_only_final_output_contracts: "Route-Only final_output Contracts"
            """When a `route_only` turn declares `final_output:`, the emitted
`final_output.contract.json` carries the same compiler-owned route target in
its top-level `route` block. See
`examples/119_route_only_final_output_contract`."""

    section shared_route_readback: "Shared route.* Readback"
        """Any emitted output may read shared compiler-owned route semantics when the
active workflow-law, `handoff_routing` law, `route_only`, `grounding`, or
review branch resolves a real route:"""
        bullets reads:
            "`route.exists`"
            "`route.next_owner`, `route.next_owner.key`, `route.next_owner.title`"
            "`route.label`, `route.summary`"

        """When every live routed branch comes from `route_from`, or when
`final_output.route:` binds a `route field` on a structured final output,
outputs may also read:"""
        bullets choice_reads:
            "`route.choice`, `route.choice.key`, `route.choice.title`, `route.choice.wire`"

        "Important rules:"
        bullets route_rules:
            """Unguarded `route.*` reads fail loud when some active branches may not
  route. Guard route-specific readback with `when route.exists:`."""
            """Guard branch-specific detail with `when route.choice == Enum.member` when
  several routed branches stay live."""
            """In authored guards, `route.exists` means a routed owner exists on the live
  branch. In emitted `final_output.contract.json`, `route.exists` means the
  final response carries route semantics at all, even when a nullable route
  field selected no handoff."""

        """See `examples/87_workflow_route_output_binding` for shared `route.*` reads
on ordinary workflow-law outputs and fail-loud unguarded route reads."""

    section generated_schema_artifacts: "Generated Schema Artifacts"
        "`emit_docs` writes structured finals alongside the agent's Markdown home:"
        bullets artifacts:
            """`schemas/<output-slug>.schema.json` — the exact lowered JSON Schema for
  the structured final output."""
            """`final_output.contract.json` — when the turn also needs final-response,
  review, route, or resolved previous-turn IO metadata. The file carries a
  top-level `route` block, a top-level `io` block, and (for reviews) a
  `review` block."""
            """`schemas/<output-slug>.schema.json` stays compliant with the OpenAI
  structured-output profile. On the current profile, object properties stay
  present on the wire, including normal fields, route fields, and
  route-field overrides."""

        """Harnesses should read the top-level `route` block in
`final_output.contract.json` for runtime routing instead of copied owner
strings in the payload."""

    section trust_surface_and_guarded_output_items: "trust_surface And Guarded Output Items"
        """`trust_surface:` on an output names the fields downstream owners may trust
as portable truth. The currentness carrier field must be listed there.

Guarded output items keep conditional readback on the output contract
itself:"""
        code:
            language: prompt-fragment
            text: """next_owner: route.next_owner when route.exists
"""
        "Guarded sections still work:"
        code:
            language: prompt-fragment
            text: """failure_detail: "Failure Detail" when verdict == ReviewVerdict.changes_requested:
    failing_gates: "Failing Gates"
        "Name the failing review gates in authored order."
"""
        "Important rules:"
        bullets trust_rules:
            """Guarded output items are still output-owned fields. They are required only
  when their guard resolves true."""
            """On ordinary outputs, guards may read declared inputs, enum members, and
  `route.exists` when the active turn resolves route semantics."""
            """On review-bound outputs, guards may also read `verdict`, `contract.*`, and
  `fields.*`."""
            """A guarded output item does not become portable truth unless it is also
  listed in `trust_surface`."""

    section pitfalls: "Pitfalls"
        bullets items:
            """Do not use `required` or `optional` inside `output schema`. The compiler
  rejects both with targeted upgrade errors (E236 and E237). Use `nullable`
  instead."""
            """Do not attach both `schema:` and `structure:` on the same markdown-bearing
  output. Pick one artifact owner."""
            """Do not read `route.*` without a guard when some branches may not route.
  Unguarded `route.*` reads fail loud."""
            """Do not compose routing by hand out of copied output fields. Use `route
  field` plus `final_output.route:` when the final JSON should own the route,
  or `route_from` when a typed selector should own it."""
            """Do not pretend a turn without a real route can still read `route.*`. If the
  turn has `current none` and no routed branch, nothing in `route.*` is live."""
            """Do not change `current_truth.invalidations` through top-level patching in
  v1. Override `current_truth` as a whole section instead."""

    section related: "Related References"
        bullets refs:
            """`references/agents-and-workflows.md` — for `final_output:` agent slot
  semantics, `handoff_routing`, `route_from`, and `route_only`."""
            """`references/reviews.md` — for review-driven `final_output` and
  `review_fields:`."""
            """`references/documents-and-tables.md` — for `structure:` attachments and
  readable block composition."""
            """`references/emit-targets.md` — for `emit_docs`, `emit_flow`, the emitted
  schema files, and `final_output.contract.json`."""

        """**Load when:** the author is shaping the turn's typed answer, wiring a
`route field`, inheriting an output, or configuring structured-final
emission."""
